69a03081-4052-4853-8d9a-79114813cd3f.17060510-40bb-41d2-87e5-9d6a3241fe35.description=
Allows a user to select how they should be notified of the outcome of a flow, and shows them a message in that way.

Inputs\:
notifyData -  The text of the notification message.
notifyMethod - The method of notification (Write to File, Email, Display or None). This value is case-insensitive.
subject - A description of what the notification is about. 
destination - The destination of the notification (email address or filename). This field is required when notifyMethod is Email or Write to File.
notificationServer - The email server to send the notification through. This field is required when notifyMethod is Email.
from - The originator of the message (email "from" address).This field is required when notifyMethod is Email.
serverPort - The port the service to notify on the server is running on. This field used when notifyMethod is Email, and it is optional (it defaults to 25 if not specified).
htmlEmail - Default value is true. The value should be true if the email is in rich text/html format. The value should be false to send the email in plain text format.

Responses\:
success - The user was notified.
failure - Notification failed.

As mentioned above, some inputs are required for certain types of notification methods. In order to schedule a flow that in turn uses this flow, all of the required fields for the given notification method must be supplied, or else the flow will not be able to execute to completion. For example, if "notifyMethod" is "File", then the "destination" input must also be specified.

69a03081-4052-4853-8d9a-79114813cd3f.2c9a5e71-07ba-4fbe-a4a3-7ab880777bd7.description=
Compares two strings, returning a true response if and only if they contain the same sequence of characters. A null string is considered to be equal to an empty string.

Inputs\:
string1 - The first string.
string2 - The second string.
ignoreCase - If set to 'true', then the comparison ignores case considerations. The two strings are considered equal ignoring case if they are of the same length and corresponding characters in the two strings are equal ignoring case. If set to any value other than 'true', then the strings must match exactly to be considered equal.

responses\:
true - If the two strings are equal
false - If the two strings are not equal

69a03081-4052-4853-8d9a-79114813cd3f.49a1ceea-6dc6-4d6f-a72f-720df766303f.description=
Synopsis

    This flow generates a volume name based on the vServer name. The volume name is generated in numeric order.
    generateVolumeName performs the following steps\:
      1. Retrieve a list of volumes based on the vServer name using the HPOO flow getVolumes.
      2. If no volumes exist, set the new volume name as VOL01 (denoting the first volume in a series).
      3. If volumes exist, sort the list of volume names in alphanumeric order.
      4. Look at the first volume on the list and determine if the net index is greater than or less than nine.
      5. Pass the volume name back to the requesting entity.

Inputs

    clusterName - The IP or host name of the NetApp cluster (required).
      Valid values\: Dot-decimal notation IPv4 address or RFC 1123 compliant host name.
      Default value\: None.

    vServerName - The name of the vServer to be used in the flow (required).
    siteId - The ID number of the site where the product is located.
    datacenter - The datacenter in which to create the customer's vServer.
      Valid values\: Implementation-specific.
      Default value\: None.

    overrideJRAS - Value to override the system defined Java RAS server.
      Valid values\: Implementation specific.
      Default value\: Hosting Eng RAS.

Results

    hpooFlowResult - The XML response specific to the functionality of the flow;  {what does this flow return and how is it returned?}  See Notes section for more details.
    flowStatus - Overall status of the flow, value is one of the string literals "success" or "failed".

Responses

    Success - All operations and subflows completed successfully.
    Failure - Some operations and/or subflows failed.

Notes

    1. Anything else the caller or support person may need to know about the flow. Relationships that aren't easily inferred, abmnormal flow behaviors, hard-codings, etc.

69a03081-4052-4853-8d9a-79114813cd3f.description=
Synopsis

A high-level Unified Compute service that finds vServers which match the siteId of a customer.

    getVserverBySiteId performs the following steps\:
      1. From the output of the getVserver flow, generate a comma-separated list of vServers that match the site ID criteria on the cluster.
      2. Count the number of vServers that match the siteID.
      3. Build an XML payload of the list of vServers to pass to the requesting entity. 

Inputs

    clusterName - The IP or host name of the NetApp cluster (required).
      Valid values\: Dot-decimal notation IPv4 address or RFC 1123 compliant host name.
      Default value\: None.

    siteId - The legacy siteId (Savvis) or BAN number for the customer (required).
      Valid values\: Implementation-specific.
      Default value\: None.

    testMode - The test mode tells the flow whether the vServer list retrieval is real (for provisioning) or a test for the process.
      Valid values\:  Literal string "true" or "false" (case ignored).
      Default value\: False.

    overrideJRAS - Value to override the system-defined Java RAS server.
      Valid values\: Implementation-specific.
      Default value\: Interpolated value of the hosteng_atlasras HPOO system property.

Results

    hpooFlowResult - The XML response specific to the functionality of the flow; returned in the HTTP POST operation envelope "hpooCallback". See Notes section for more details.
    flowStatus - Overall status of the flow, where the value is one of the string literals "success" or "failed".

Responses

    Success - All operations and subflows completed successfully.
    Failure - Some operations and/or subflows failed.

Notes

    1. vServer name matching\: getVserverBySiteId finds all vServers on the cluster matching the pattern name ${siteId}NAS.
        
            Example\: If a customer has a siteID of S654321, then, for example vServers named S654321SL7NAS01 and S654321SL7NAS03, would match the criteria.

    2. Example vServer return XML element\:

        S001653SL7NAS01

    3. Example XML payload returned to the callbackEndpoint, where siteId is S001652\:

        
            1111
            222
            a77ce74b-badf-419d-9574-8285983fbfd7
            success
            
                
                     S001652SL7NAS01
                     S001652SL7NAS02
                     S001652SL7NAS03
